  "text": "You have a preview view of this article while we are checking your access. When we have confirmed access, the full article content will load.Karah Preiss and Emma Roberts were among the people at Chateau Marmont celebrating Lili Anolik’s upcoming book “Didion \u0026 Babitz.”Credit...Krista Schlueter for The New York TimesOut \u0026 AboutLetters of a Literary Titan Read by Da’Vine Joy Randolph, Emma Roberts and MoreAn event at L.A.’s Chateau Marmont celebrated an upcoming book about Eve Babitz and Joan Didion, two writers who documented the magic of California.Karah Preiss and Emma Roberts were among the people at Chateau Marmont celebrating Lili Anolik’s upcoming book “Didion \u0026 Babitz.”Credit...Krista Schlueter for The New York TimesJulia CarmelJulia Carmel reported from Los Angeles for Out \u0026 About, a column that covers the events where notable, powerful and influential figures gather — and their outfits.Nov. 14, 2024The gothic, candelabra-lit parlor of the Chateau Marmont was buzzing on Tuesday evening with tequila and celebrity gossip from the 1960s — a fitting scene for a release party of Lili Anolik’s new book, “Didion \u0026 Babitz.”The dual-biography, which draws parallels between Joan Didion and Eve Babitz, two Californian writers who partied in Hollywood throughout the 1960s and ’70s and died within days of each other in December 2021, is one of 2024’s most anticipated releases, snagging endorsements from celebrities like Lena Dunham and Emma Roberts.Though the book technically is about both Ms. Babitz and Ms. Didion — the literary giants who documented the culture and glamour of California — the night was squarely centered around Ms. Babitz, who frequented the Chateau and has experienced a renaissance in recent years.“She’s hard not to love,” said the actress Nicole Richie. “I fell in love with her when she wrote ‘Sex and Rage.’ It’s just a fun ride.”ImageThe actress Elizabeth Olsen.Credit...Krista Schlueter for The New York TimesImageThe actress Da’Vine Joy Randolph.Credit...Krista Schlueter for The New York TimesImageThe actress Alexi Wasser.Credit...Krista Schlueter for The New York TimesThank you for your patience while we verify access. If you are in Reader mode please exit and log into your Times account, or subscribe for all of The Times.Thank you for your patience while we verify access.Already a subscriber? Log in.Want all of The Times? Subscribe.AdvertisementSKIP ADVERTISEMENT",
